  "sphere_commentary": {
    "run_date": "2026-04-28",
    "overview": "All series show strong efficacy signals, with HEALING and THRIVING outperforming TRANSFORMING, but with notable protocol-level variations.\n• HEALING (n=574, mean=6.98) demonstrates consistent DESCENT efficacy across anxiety/sleep/overstim entries.\n• THRIVING (n=245) achieves slightly higher mean (6.96) with HOLD protocols excelling in focus/clarity (T-FC-L3: 7.63).\n• TRANSFORMING (n=181) shows lower mean (6.59) and highest variance (std=1.87), particularly in ASCENT motivation protocols.",
    "cross_series": "Series performance aligns with design intent, but with meaningful differences in implementation and outcomes.\n• HEALING shows tightest variance (std=1.77) and strong anxiety entry protocol (H-AX-L1: 7.22).\n• THRIVING displays high focus/clarity gains (T-FC-L3: 7.63) but with smaller samples (n<40).\n• TRANSFORMING's ASCENT protocols have lowest means (X-MD-L1: 6.36) with polarized responses.",
    "anomalies": "Several protocols show marked discrepancy between predicted and observed outcomes or unexpected distribution patterns.\n• X-MC-L3 (mean=5.7, std=2.45) shows extreme bimodality with developing confidence (n=10).\n• T-FC-L1 demonstrates analytical isolation (mean_sim=0.772) despite high predicted efficacy (7.728).\n• H-CR-L2 has high AutoGluon score (7.955) but only 6.52 observed mean from 33 listeners.\n• Note: These suggest either population mismatch or protocol parameter misalignment.",
    "development_signals": "Priority actions to optimize protocol design and routing based on convergent signals.\n• [CONVERGENT SIGNAL] Promote X-ME-L1/X-ME-L2 (THRIVING mood protocols) across additional zones — 4/5 analyzers highlight cross-bucket efficacy potential.\n• Investigate H-CR-L2 (crisis protocol) with AutoGluon's high predicted score (7.955) but low observed mean — recommend adjusting adviser routing and groove depth.\n• Create L2 variant of T-FC-L3 (n=35) with slightly reduced intensity for broader THRIVING access — 3 analysts cite drift and variance patterns.\n• Adjust X-MD-L3 ASCENT curve steepness following the outlier success (mean=7.15) in motivation protocol.",
    "embedding_analysis": "High analytical drift across runs suggests evolving data patterns, with clusters confirming category coherence.\n• CROSS-RUN DRIFT: 24 protocols show sim<0.85 (most concerning: T-FC-L3 sim=0.661) indicating instability.\n• SEMANTIC CLUSTERS: X-ME-L1↔X-ME-L2 (sim=0.966) and T-CF-L1↔T-CF-L2 (0.961) confirm category coherence.\n• Confidence: Drift analysis is reliable (high run count) but semantic stability remains low.",
